\begin_layout aEnumerate (ClassicThesis)
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 is an 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}_{1}$
\end_inset

-measurable random variable valued in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{R}^{k}$
\end_inset

 representing 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 functionals of the path being conditioned and
\end_layout

\begin_layout aEnumerate (ClassicThesis)
\begin_inset Formula $\nu$
\end_inset

 is a law representing the conditioning, 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Definition
such that, if the law of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 under 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}$
