\begin_layout Standard
From this point on, we will always assume that the tuples 
\begin_inset Formula $(Y,\nu)$
\end_inset

 we encounter satisfy the conditions above.
 The next result demonstrates the existence and uniqueness of a measure
 which satisfies intuitive notions of what it means to condition a measure
 on the law of a random variable.
 Moreover, it says that such a conditioned measure is the convex diversity
 minimizing measure with respect to a family of related probability measures.
\end_layout

